Q1/- What is a Servlet ? What is the role of the DispatcherServlet in the Spring boot rest 
     application.
     
Answer:- Servlet is a class in the SpringBoot which capture the user input and Validate it,
         Also Instead of generating data directly to the user it keeps data to the repository 
         and forward the control to the JSP.
         
         Spring frameWork provides Spring-web-mvc module to simplify the manual mvc application 
         development.In which, Spring mvc module provides a predefined Servlet class with 
         predefined flow control logic,i.e, DispatcherServlet class.
         
         DispatcherServlet simplify the process of developing java based webApplication/webService
         with predefined flow control.It 
         
         
          
          
          
